Dear Mommy …. 

Its been 4 months since you left and every day feels like a never-ending battle. I miss your hugs when u would lick my face and say some funny gay shit, your comforting words every-time I was confused or lost and mostly the unconditional love you gave me for 28 non stop years. I dont know who to even be without you I struggle to even look in the mirror because Idk who im looking at.
I try to find strength in the memories we shared and the love you instilled in me but its so hard ma. Most days I wake up feeling like i can’t keep going but then you remind me that I can. I know you see the roller coaster of emotions im on. Crying myself to sleep every night to laugh through pain all day 🥺. I learned so much about GOD since you departed and how much he will take on for me and how much I can lean on him. I miss you more then you can ever imagine. Ma you weren’t just my parent you were my friend, my diary, my twin ,my protector, my light EVERY TIME it got dark you were my reason to live all them times i felt like I didn’t have one. We were a DYNAMIC duo from 1995.- 2023 Thank You for being the worlds Greatest mom a daughter could ever ask for 💝
(Just look at how we look at each other ❤️)
I know its gone be a longgg time before im okay but ma I promise you ima get there. For now just hold my hand those days you see me struggling to smile 💔
